  "title": "Quality Control Executive/Assistant (Food Manufacturing) - SS10",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Quality Control Executive</strong></li><li>Woodlands</li><li>$2,700 - $3,000</li><li>5 days Mon to Fri</li><li>Working time: 8.30am to 5.30pm</li></ul><p><strong>Job scopes: </strong></p><p>1. Factory equipment cleanliness inspection before production.</p><p>2. Conduct thorough checks on raw materials and finished products for quality, including microbial, sensory, and visual assessments.</p><p>3. Promptly report any quality issues to supervisors for investigation and resolution.</p><p>4. Collaborate with other departments to schedule material inspections and sampling.</p><p>5. Verify certificates to ensure raw materials meet standards before use.</p><p>6. Provide training for new staff members.</p><p>7. Assist with audits, both internal and external.</p><p>8. Maintain accurate records.</p><p>9. Perform equipment calibration as required.</p><p>10. Manage inventory and uphold lab cleanliness.</p><p>11. Issue Certificates of Analysis for materials and products.</p><p>12. Support with additional tasks assigned by the company.</p><p>13. Oversees the overall quality control function</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Nitec/Higher Nitec/Diploma in Food Science and Technology, Food, Nutrition & Culinary science related.</li><li>At least 1 year experience in food industry / manufacturing</li></ul><p>Samuel Siaw</p><p>The Supreme HR Advisory Pte Ltd</p><p>EA No: 14C7279</p><p>Reg No: R2412474</p><p></p>",
